kind of thing, but as continuing to give direction 
to Scripps Institution of Oceanography, which he

17:02.656 --> 17:17.820
thought would be his major contribution to the 
scientific world. I take it from reading your

17:17.840 --> 17:21.285
publication list, you don't see your role that 
way. Is that a fair statement? It is a fair

17:23.048 --> 17:24.089
statement. And I think you've got to keep several 
things in mind. The facility that he administers

17:26.714 --> 17:29.658
is considerably larger. Yes. and I can see why it 
would be constantly threatening what little time

17:30.972 --> 17:39.880
he might have had left for research. This 
institution in my lifetime will never approach

17:39.900 --> 17:49.408
the size of his, in part by coincidence and in part 
because we don't want it to. We operate on the theme

17:50.429 --> 18:00.237
that a university facility like this functions 
best in some nebulous size range which we've not

17:50.429 --> 18:00.237
really defined. But the relationship between 
staff and students, students and students, is so

18:00.487 --> 18:11.944
important here that we don't want it to be the size 
of something that he's dealing with. So it's a

18:12.905 --> 18:14.728
different ballgame entirely.

